quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  32,1,"Alif Lām Mīm."
  32,2,"The bestowal of the Scripture from on high is—no doubt about it—by the Lord of all realms."
  32,3,"Yet they say, “He has fabricated it.” Rather, it is the truth from your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord, so that you may warn a people to whom no warner came before you, that they may be guided."
  32,4,"Allah is the One Who created the heavens and the earth and whatever is between them in six days{1}, and then settled over the Throne; apart from Him, you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>have neither ally nor intercessor. Will you not remind yourselves?",footnotes:1:Six equal intervals of time, which may be six heavenly days, each of them being 1000 earthly years long (see 22:47).
  32,5,"He governs every matter from the heavens to the earth, then it ascends to Him on a day the length of which is a thousand years by your<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>count."
  32,6,"That is the Knower of the hidden realm and the manifest, the Almighty, the Bestower of mercy"
  32,7,"Who has made <span class=""h"">excellent everything He created<sup foot_note=""80847"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>, and He originated the creation of man from clay,"
  32,8,"then made his progeny from an extract of a despicable fluid,"
  32,9,"then He proportioned him and breathed into him of His Spirit, and He gave you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>hearing and sight<i class=""s"">(s) </i>and burning hearts; little do you give thanks."
  32,10,"And they said, “<span class=""h"">Can it be that</span>when we have becomelost into the earth—<span class=""h"">can it be that</span>we will<sup foot_note=""80848"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup>reallybe brought to a new creation?” Rather, they do deny the meeting with their Lord."
  32,11,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “The angel of death put in charge of you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>takes you, then to your Lord <span class=""h"">you are returned<sup foot_note=""80849"" class=""qiraat"">1</sup> </span>.”"
